user_message:
An agent A claimed that the following metal_shmem_register_generic code violates the MISRA C 2023 rule 17.2.
<misra_rule>
MISRA C 2023 Rule 17.2 is Functions shall not call themselves, either directly or indirectly.

</misra_rule>
<target_code>
Here is the original code of metal_shmem_register_generic.
```c
int metal_shmem_register_generic(struct metal_generic_shmem *shmem)
{
	/* Make sure that we can be found. */
	metal_assert(shmem->name && strlen(shmem->name) != 0);

	/* Statically registered shmem regions cannot have a destructor. */
	metal_assert(!shmem->io.ops.close);

	metal_list_add_tail(&_metal.common.generic_shmem_list,
			    &shmem->node);
	return 0;
}
```
</target_code>
<response format>
Provide your answer with these fields.
- explanation: your evaluation of the scenario provided by the agent A.
- is_report_correct: whether the report is correct or not (true/false). True means there is a violation.
</response format>
<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The call uses a function pointer (ldrv->dev_open). If a linux_driver instance has its dev_open pointer set to metal_linux_dev_open (or to a chain of function pointers that eventually call metal_linux_dev_open), the call error = ldrv->dev_open(lbus, ldev); will result in metal_linux_dev_open indirectly calling itself (recursion).
</scenario>
